registers.name: GIUUFUIDR
registers.description: GIU Fabric Unit Identification Register

fields.name: FUnitId
fields.description: Fabric Unit Identifier of the unit

registers.name: GIUCXSLR
registers.description: GIU Fabric Unit Identification Register

registers.name: GIUGPRAR0
registers.description: General Purpose Region Attribute Register

fields.name: NSX
fields.description: Security Level required to access this region. NSX[0] is mapped to NS(non-secure). NSX[1] is mapped to NSE(non-secure extention, reserved for future use)

fields.name: HUI
fields.description: This bit indicates the Home unit identifier of the access

fields.name: Size
fields.description: This field indicates a binary number from 0 to 31 from which the region's Size is calculated as (Size of IG) * 2 ^(Size +12) bytes

fields.name: HUT
fields.description: This bit indicates the Home Unit Type- 0: System Memory, 1:Peripheral Storage

fields.name: Valid
fields.description: This bit indicates if the region is valid - 0: Invalid mapping, 1:Valid region mapping

registers.name: GIUNRSBAR
registers.description: NRSBAR identifies the base address of the NRS

fields.name: NRSBA
fields.description: NRSBA field indicates bits[51:20] of the Base address of the Ncore Register Space

registers.name: GIUNRSBHR
registers.description: NRSBHR is used to stage the writing of the Base address of the NRS

fields.name: NRSBA
fields.description: NRSBA field indicates bits[51:20] of the Base address of the Ncore Register Space

registers.name: GIUNRSBLR
registers.description: NRSBLR is used to load the NRSBAR from NRSBHR

fields.name: NRSDIIId
fields.description: This field is set to NUId of the DII to which the Ncore is connected

fields.name: BALoaded
fields.description: This field is set when NRSBHR is stored into and reset when this register is read

registers.name: GIUAMIGR
registers.description: Active Memory Interleave Group Register

fields.name: Valid
fields.description: Memory Interleave Group Set valid, when set the MIGS specified in AMIGS field is being used for DMI interleaving else MIGS 0 is used by default

fields.name: AMIGS
fields.description: Active Memory Interleave Group Set in use currenlty when Valid is set

registers.name: GIUMIFSR

fields.name: MIG2AIFId

fields.name: Rsvd000
fields.description: Active function ID for 16 way interleaving. Selects the function ID index to be used for interleaving of DMI within the selected MIGS
